        "subject": "LU-20191 efalnd: fix module refcount leak on base startup",
        "message": "LU-20191 efalnd: fix module refcount leak on base startup\n\nThe base startup takes a module reference but the error paths never\nrelease it, leaking the reference. This makes the module unremovable\nafter a failed base startup. Add a new error label that releases the\nmodule reference on all error paths where it was successfully taken.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nChange-Id: Ic6a59eba0774fa1f6103387070413758f6e0849c\nSigned-off-by: Tom Sela <tomsela@amazon.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
